article.headline: Alabama A&amp,M 62, Prairie View 53
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas -- Cornelius Hester scored 15 points and Casey Cantey posted 11 points and 11 rebounds to lead Alabama A&M past Prairie View A&M 62-53 on Monday night. The Bulldogs (9-9, 6-3 SWAC) used a 14-2 run early in the second half to open a 41-27 lead, their largest of the game. Prairie View (6-16, 3-6) came no closer than five points and not until the final 1:05. Bo Amusa had 10 points, six during the momentum-changing run, for Alabama A&M. Hester also had four steals. Brandon Webb and Michael Griffin were the top scorers for the Panthers with eight points apiece. Griffin also had eight rebounds and four assists.
